    "An additional production channel, NH 2 + CH 4 → CH 3 + NH 3, is also active on both limbs, highlighting the role of hydrocarbon chemistry in nitrogen coupling.",
    "In the 1D RCE model, NH 3 formation is primarily driven by NH 2 + H 2 → NH 3 + H and the three-body reaction H + NH 2 + M → NH 3 + M, reflecting more efficient recombination under smoother vertical gradients and higher pressures.",
